header.gameNote: LENAPE TRAIL CLASSIC AT ATLANTIC CITY NJ

article.headline: Cincinnati 80, Temple 71
article.story: ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Marcus Sikes and Deonta Vaughn each scored 17 points, and Cincinnati rallied from a 16-point deficit to beat Temple 80-71 at the Atlantic City Lenape Trail Classic at Boardwalk Hall on Saturday. John Williamson added 15 points and 13 rebounds for the Bearcats (6-2), who were playing their first road game of the season. Semaj Inge scored 17 points, Dustin Salisbery added 18, and Dionte Christmas 20 for the Owls (3-3), who had their three-game winning streak halted. Temple got 14 first-half points from Christmas and 12 each from Salisbery and Inge, postings its highest first-half scoring total of the season and carrying a 46-39 lead at the break. Cincinnati capitalized on Temple's cold second-half shooting. The Bearcats went on an 18-0 run while the Owls went without a field goal for just over 10 minutes and took the lead with 7:43 remaining. Sikes and Williamson combined to score 11 points in the run. Temple, which shot 4-for-8 from 3-point range in the first half, shot 1-for-11 over the final 20 minutes. The last time the teams met, on February 22, 2000, Temple beat the then top-ranked Cincinnati 77-69.
